model.name: ClusterCloud
model.documentation: Specification of a on-prem container cluster based on Raspberry PI 3 architecture.

element.name: distributed system development support
element.documentation: Support the development of distributed systems, applications, and components

element.name: interface for container and application management
element.documentation: A GUI should be provided for the management of nodes, applications, and images

element.name: scaling of storage and compute across nodes
element.documentation: Storage and compute can be added dynamically based on adding a new worker or manager node, higher capacity SD card, etc

element.name: hot swappable SD card support
element.documentation: Storage system should be built such that once n+1 environment is up, storage can be incrementally increased by failing a storage physical device, replacing with a larger capacity device, and adding back into cluster.

element.name: ARM architecture
element.documentation: ARM architecture of Raspberry PI limits available docker images and packages

element.name: Phase 2 - Conversion of static images to specifications
Phase 3 - Clean build of worker from specification (automated)
Phase 2a - Creation of worker join scripts / services
Phase 4 - Build of multiple workers / dynamic cluster provisioning

view.name: GPIO Hardware IMPL
view.documentation: Implementation of hardware notification of node status via RPI LED

view.name: Work Packages
view.documentation: Description of major work packages and deliverables
